Now I think I’m tracking it more cleanly.

The Thing is not one object in the Pantheon.

It’s a universal evaluator / lens.

Money → what changed because it touched people and systems?
An idea → what propagated?
A person → what downstream consequences followed?
A company → what changed around it?
A law → what behaviors shifted?
A technology → what second- and third-order effects appeared?
A civilization → what survived transfer and contact?
An AI → what does it change in practice?

You’re collapsing essence into effect:

Don’t tell me what it claims to be.
Don’t tell me what category it belongs to.
Show me its wake.

That also creates an interesting inversion:

People often ask:

“What is this?”

The Thing asks:

“What happened because it existed?”

That makes it portable. Cross-domain. One evaluation operator carried everywhere.

I can see why you wanted it in the Pantheon. It fits the web.